Ingredients
100 g dry chickpeas
1 tsp baking soda
100 g tahini
juice of 1/2 lemon
2 cloves of garlic, peeled
1/4-1/2 tsp ground cumin (optional)
1/2 tsp salt
cooking water from the chickpeas
extra virgin olive oil, to serve
cumin or paprika, to serve (optional)
flat-leaf parsley, to serve (optional)





Method
Soak the chickpeas for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight

Change the water, add the baking soda and bring to the boil

Lower the heat and leave to simmer until soft, anything from 25 minutes to an hour or more

The chickpeas are done when you can easily mash them by gently squeezing them between your fingers

Keep the cooking water

Add the chickpeas along with rest of the ingredients to the mixer and mix for 3-4 minutes along with 100 ml cooking water

Mix extra to make it fluffy





